    "page": 37,
    "title": "Motivators Hierarchy",
    "content": "Motivators Hierarchy\nYour motivation to succeed in anything you do is determined by your underlying\nmotivators. You will feel energized and successful at work when your job supports\nyour personal motivators. They are listed below from the highest to the lowest.\n1. Individualistic/Political - Rewards those who value personal\nrecognition, freedom, and control over their own destiny and others.\n5.5*\n2. Aesthetic - Rewards those who value balance in their lives, creative\nself-expression, beauty and nature.\n4.3*\n3. Theoretical - Rewards those who value knowledge for knowledge's\nsake, continuing education and intellectual growth.\n6.0\n4. Social - Rewards those who value opportunities to be of service to\nothers and contribute to the progress and well being of society.\n4.2\n5. Utilitarian/Economic - Rewards those who value practical\naccomplishments, results and rewards for their investments of time,\nresources and energy.\n5.3*\n6. Traditional/Regulatory - Rewards those who value traditions\ninherent in social structure,\nrules, regulations and principles.\n4.7*\n5.8\n5.8\n5.5\n5.5\n4.2\n3.2\nTRADITIONAL\nTHEORETICAL\nMI: 45-37-47-45-47-31 (THE.-UTI.-AES.-SOC.-IND.-TRA.)\n* 68% of the population falls within the shaded area.\nAESTHETIC\nINDIVIDUALISTIC\nCopyright © 2006-2015. Target Training International, Ltd. 36"
